parameters:
Chancellor: What's this? I hear reports of an intruder
causing a ruckus, and who do I find but you? Quite the late
arrival, aren't we, knight?
Chancellor... it was all your scheme...!

Chancellor: How did your search for the holy sword fare?
Kukuku... Did you find the non-existent blade?

Chancellor: Hmph, this is the problem with knights... always
so hot-blooded.

I'm relieved to see that even after a long tenure as
Chancellor, your body has not grown dull. Now I can strike
you down without holding back.

Chancellor: Isn't it your own body that has grown dull?
What's wrong, your movements lack sharpness?

Chancellor: Did 'something' happen on your way here? For
example, something like... the dignity residing in a woman's
body being trampled upon.

Chancellor: Overindulging in madness is something to
consider. When only instincts are laid bare, further
adjustments are necessary.
00_st_pri_a01
Princess: Ugh... uhh... ah...!!
Princess: Is there... someone there? Ugh... aah...!!
Ah, Princess!?
What in the world...

You bastard Chancellor!! To lay hands on your own
sovereign!!
Chancellor: Hmph. I never once considered that girl my lord.

Chancellor: The only one I ever swore loyalty to was the
previous king alone.
You are such a person...!

Chancellor: By the way, Reisha, did you read the documents
in my study?
The memoirs in the study?

If you wish to skip content due to repetition, I recommend
selecting "I read it." If you are interested in the story,
select "I haven't read it."
I've read it.
I haven't read it.
読んだ。

Chancellor: I see, that makes things quicker and easier for
me.
説明スキップ
読んでいない。

Chancellor: Why I would lay hands on the princess, you ask?
If you wish to know, I shall tell you. Now then... where
should I begin?

Chancellor: Tell me, Reisha, do you know? There is a secret
within the royal bloodline.
A secret, you say...?

Chancellor: Why does the Near Lake royal family have so many
short-lived members? Why are there inherent differences in
the line of succession from birth?

Chancellor: The fact that many past kings, upon beginning to
exhibit their talents, would rage violently and meet tragic
ends if their brilliance was too strong.

Chancellor: The words of regret that slipped from the lips
of His Highness the Crown Prince amidst the recent
succession turmoil, 'My royal blood is thin.'

Chancellor: The illness of His Highness the Crown Prince,
the defection of His Highness the elder brother, the
uncharacteristic fury and subsequent death of the wise
previous king.

Chancellor: His Highness's words made many things click into
place for me. Since that day I heard them, I've been
obsessed with the royal blood.

Chancellor: The existence of a special magical power
mediated by blood. A secret magic that lies dormant within
certain lineages and is passed down through generations.

Chancellor: Utilizing my position and gaining collaborators,
my research advanced. The relationship between blood flowing
within humans and magic reached profound depths.
Chancellor: But what of it?

Chancellor: The one girl who solely possesses the royal
bloodline I most wanted to understand was closest to me, yet
her temperament was farthest from what I desired. Isn't it
laughable?

Chancellor: She doesn't sway with profit nor tolerate
deceit. She maintains an unwavering stance of loving her
country sincerely. She must know full well that without my
connections and skills, governance would falter.
Chancellor: It was quite a struggle to win her over.

Chancellor: She was a sullen princess difficult to handle,
but why is it, Reisha? The moment I mention your name, she
becomes eager. You are greatly trusted by her.

Chancellor: She listened intently with shining eyes when I
spoke of our time at the court school where I briefly
instructed you. Such an innocent thing. Unaware of what fate
would befall her afterwards.

Chancellor: To capture her... perhaps that sounds too harsh.
Let's say I invited her here to cooperate with our magical
experiments and then it became clear.

Chancellor: The legendary sword "Sword of Dawn" mentioned in
the royal family's lore. Its radiance is said to lead the
country to dawn as a supreme treasure, that's its true
nature.

Chancellor: It is said that the kings of generations who
awakened the power of magic with their particularly strong
royal bloodline were able to extract and materialize immense
magical power from their own blood.

Chancellor: The blood-soaked sword overwhelms everything,
and with the greatest power of its time, it thunders
domination upon the land. Its form, turning battlefields
into scorched earth and mowing down enemy soldiers, is a
weapon itself. To think such a thing is considered a supreme
treasure.

Chancellor: It's laughable, isn't it? The royal family's
supreme treasure, thought to be lost, is in my hands, and
yet, despite that, it has been forgotten by all, and the
country is thus declining.

Chancellor: Have you ever experienced it? The feeling of
being able to do nothing but watch as the country you
believe in weakens.

Chancellor: That's exactly why I will revive it. I will
awaken the royal blood and with magic, I will make this
country resound throughout the world!!

Chancellor: I will take that first step towards domination
that the previous king I swore loyalty to could not
achieve!!
説明スキップ
Chancellor: For my plans, your existence was an obstacle.

Chancellor: You live by the knightly spirit of this country,
not swayed by profit and sticking to righteousness. I knew
you would never lend an ear to my true intentions.

Chancellor: It would be troublesome if it caused a
commotion. Before my plans were discovered, I wanted to take
care of this little problem when some useful information
came in.

Chancellor: It would be good if I could send your existence
far away; even better if you perish on your journey. A
knight abandoning their mission and returning empty-handed
is something you would never allow yourself.

Chancellor: "You" will obey if it's "for the lord," and "our
king" will easily accept my opinion if it's "for the
knight."

Chancellor: Bonds and emotions can sometimes cloud one's
eyes, you half-baked lot.

Is that all you have to say? Are you planning to give a
speech now?

I understand what you want to say. If you're expecting me to
panic and reconsider at this point, then you're sadly
mistaken.

If buying time is your aim, it's transparent. I won't ask
you to change your mind now. The sights I've witnessed are
more than enough to condemn you.

Value the fact that I haven't sent my sword flying at you
already...!!

Chancellor: Hmph, so be it. This is why knights are
problematic. Always quick to fight, first and foremost.

Chancellor: Although, as it stands now, I am in the position
of a knight protecting the monarch. The first step towards
my domination. I've finally obtained it; there's no way I'm
giving it back!

I will never allow you to speak of chivalry with that
mouth!!

Chancellor: Unable to sense danger, the monarch you should
protect is exposed to peril, and on top of that, you rush
about on a journey orchestrated to search for a non-existent
holy sword.

Chancellor: What else can this be called but foolishness? If
such a thing is called knighthood, then I have no need for
it.
Gah...!

Chancellor: Though we've been apart for a long time, do not
forget that I too once took up the sword and fought for the
country.
Chancellor: Although, strictly speaking...
Chancellor: My true talent lay in this direction.

To our lord... no, not just that. For the many sins
committed by your hands against those you've harmed, your
body has more than enough to atone for.
Do not think your past atrocities will ever be forgiven—!!
Chancellor: Do not underestimate me, you outdated knight!

Chancellor: The time for the awakening of the royal
bloodline is near! If you intend to interfere with my plans,
I shall show no mercy—!
Chancellor: Here I go...—!!
